title: About
text:
Hello! I’m Rowshni Farnaz Fatema, a passionate student of Business Analytics in the Department of Econometrics and Business Statistics at Monash University. With a keen interest in data-driven decision making, my academic journey has equipped me with strong analytical and problem-solving skills, enabling me to transform data into actionable insights.
I am particularly enthusiastic about areas such as data visualization, machine learning, and statistical modeling, which play a critical role in solving real-world business problems. My goal is to leverage my expertise to make meaningful contributions in the field of data analytics.

title: Welcome To My Blog Template
text:
From Flying Saucers to Modern Mysteries: The Evolution of UFO Sightings Published on October 3, 2024 By Rowshni Farnaz Fatema
Introduction Unidentified Flying Objects (UFOs) have captivated the world for decades. From the iconic “flying saucer” sightings of the 1940s to modern-day reports, the mystery of UFOs continues to fascinate. This blog explores the patterns and peaks of UFO sightings over time and highlights the cultural and historical factors that have influenced public interest in UFOs.
Problem Description The goal of this analysis is to understand how UFO sightings have evolved over the past 70 years. Are these sightings linked to historical events, or is the public simply fascinated by the unknown? By examining data from various time periods, we can gain insights into the underlying trends and patterns of UFO sightings.
This is the first post in a Quarto blog. Welcome!
